OL,3,C'WRU's Julius Caesar? Never
OL,4,Cunderestimate Welsh rugby's penchant
OL,5,Cfor mayhem'
OL,7,FRichard Collier-Keywood and Julius
OL,8,FCaesar might have had their
OL,9,Fdifferences, but indulge me for a
OL,10,Fmoment.
OL,12,FWhen Caesar fell, his assassins
OL,13,Fbelieved they had killed not only the
OL,14,Fman, but the movement. Rome proved
OL,15,Fthem wrong.
OL,17,FCaesar's allies regrouped and, in
OL,18,Ftime, the Empire was reshaped in his
OL,19,Fimage.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/11
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
